PRISCO v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 14, 1923.) No. 155. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Anthony Prisco was convicted of an offense, and he brings error. Affirmed. David P. Siegel and Nathan -Lieberman, both of New York City, for plaintiff in error. William Hayward, U. S. Atty., and Abraham I. Menin, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of New York City.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and MAYEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
